The following runtime scripts are reused, largely verbatim, to preserve the
exact environment-variable contract (ACCESS_TOKEN, APP_ID/APP_PRIVATE_KEY,
RUNNER_SCOPE, ORG_NAME, RUNNER_NAME, RUNNER_LABELS, EPHEMERAL, ...) so this
image remains a drop-in replacement:

  * scripts/entrypoint.sh
  * scripts/token.sh
  * scripts/app_token.sh
  * scripts/install_actions.sh (modified: adds checksum verification)

The Dockerfile and scripts/install-tools.sh are original work whose purpose is
to remove the vulnerability cluster present in the upstream image. See README
"Security" for details.
